# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and adjust values. Never commit real secrets.
#
# Runtime: the app uses a single active URL, `DATABASE_URL`. There is no multi-DB switch in code.
# Convention for optional dev RDS: keep `DATABASE_URL_RDS_DEV` here as a reference, and when you
# want the app and Prisma to hit RDS, copy that value into `DATABASE_URL` in `.env.local` (or
# maintain two blocks and comment/uncomment). Always confirm the target before destructive migrations.

# --- Primary local dev: Docker Compose Postgres (see docker-compose.yml) ---
# Matches default POSTGRES_USER / POSTGRES_PASSWORD / POSTGRES_DB in compose unless you changed them.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://scripturelm:scripturelm_dev_password@localhost:5433/scripturelm?schema=public"

# --- Optional: cloud dev RDS (same schema/migrations; AWS-parity checks) ---
# Uncomment and set when you have a dev RDS instance with pgvector. To use it, copy this URL into
# DATABASE_URL above (or swap commented blocks). Ensure your machine can reach RDS (security group/VPN).
# DATABASE_URL_RDS_DEV="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@your-dev-rds.region.rds.amazonaws.com:5432/DBNAME?schema=public"
